victions, physical abuse, and killings of unarmed civilians.</p><p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 1em; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 14px; text-size-adjust: 100%; vertical-align: baseline; background: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgb(102, 102, 102); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, Arial, sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 500; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;"><img src="https://cochranfirmlaw.com/storage/blogs/img84.jpg" style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px auto; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 14px; text-size-adjust: 100%; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; max-width: 100%; height: auto; display: block;"></p><h1 style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 10px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 30px; text-size-adjust: 100%; vertical-align: baseline; background: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgb(51, 51, 51); line-height: 1em; font-weight: 500; font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, Arial, sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;"><br></h1><ul style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 23px 1em; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 14px; text-size-adjust: 100%; vertical-align: baseline; background: rgb(255, 255, 255); list-style: disc; line-height: 26px; color: rgb(102, 102, 102); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, Arial, sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 500; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;"><li style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 14px; text-size-adjust: 100%; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;"><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 14px; text-size-adjust: 100%; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; font-weight: bold;">Police Officers are accused of beating a group of people</strong></li></ul><p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 1em; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 14px; text-size-adjust: 100%; vertical-align: baseline; background: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgb(102, 102, 102); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, Arial, sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 500; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">EI Monte Police officers are accused of beating a group of people, who have complained about $6 million in compensation. According to their lawyer, the group was standing out in the backyard of their residential apartment when a car drew up, the driver got out and climbed a fence. The attitude of police department violence in El Monte is widespread, and it must be addressed. An allegation has been filed as a prelude to a lawsuit.&nbsp;</p><ul style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 23px 1em; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 14px; text-size-adjust: 100%; vertical-align: baseline; background: rgb(255, 255, 255); list-style: disc; line-height: 26px; color: rgb(102, 102, 102); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, Arial, sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 500; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;"><li style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 14px; text-size-adjust: 100%; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;"><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 14px; text-size-adjust: 100%; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; font-weight: bold;">Monte Police Officer Assaulted a Man</strong></li></ul><p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 1em; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 14px; text-size-adjust: 100%; vertical-align: baseline; background: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgb(102, 102, 102); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, Arial, sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 500; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">A court has awarded more than $1.2 million to a person assaulted by an EI Monte police officer who seized him for possessing an expired car license. Montes, a Lancaster resident, alleges Duran pulled his gun on him outside the M Motel at 11 a.m. on Sept. 30, 2018, during an argument over outdated registration plates. These types of illegal and terrible activities violate the constitutional rights and freedom of the citizens of EI Monte, CA, As a result, the citizens cannot be able to trust the police officers.</p><p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 1em; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 14px; text-size-adjust: 100%; vertical-align: baseline; background: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgb(102, 102, 102); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, Arial, sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 500; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;"><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 14px; text-size-adjust: 100%; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; font-weight: bold;">What to do when one is becoming a victim of Police Brutality?</strong></p><p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 1em; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 14px; text-size-adjust: 100%; vertical-align: baseline; background: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgb(102, 102, 102); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, Arial, sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 500; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">Citizens of EI Monte, California, should be conscious of unlawful traits involving police brutality and take necessary measures against them. Citizens must file a complaint against police brutality in the court of justice. The term “color of law” alludes to an act performed under the impression of judicial authorization when no such power existed. The terminology is used in the federal Civil Rights Legislation, which provides EI Monte citizens the rights to prosecute government authorities and their representatives who use their authority to infringe constitutionally granted liberties and states:</p><p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 1em; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 14px; text-size-adjust: 100%; vertical-align: baseline; background: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgb(102, 102, 102); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, Arial, sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 500; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">“Any individual who, under color of any law, statute, culture, or usage of any region or municipal, subjects, or causes to be subjected, any resident of the United States, including El Monte, CA, or any other individual within the authority thereof, to the neglect of any privileges, rights, or legal protections secured by the Laws and constitution, shall be legally responsible to the party harmed in an activity at law, suit in equity, or other adequate proceedings for redress.”</p><p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 1em; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 14px; text-size-adjust: 100%; vertical-align: baseline; background: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgb(102, 102, 102); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, Arial, sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 500; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: 